{{Infobox government agency |agency_name = Thailand Institute of Nuclear Technology |type = Public organization |nativename_a = {{lang|th|สถาบันเทคโนโลยีนิวเคลียร์แห่งชาติ}} |nativename_r = |logo = Tint-logo-01a.png |logo_width = |logo_caption = |seal = |seal_width = |seal_caption = |picture = |picture_width = |picture_caption = |formed = 2006 |jurisdiction = [[Government of Thailand]] |headquarters = [[Bangkok]], [[Thailand]] |region_code = |coordinates = |employees = |budget = |chief1_name =Dr. Pornthep Nisamaneepong (CEO) |chief1_position = |agency_type = research institute |parent_department = [[Ministry of Science and Technology (Thailand)|Ministry of Science and Technology]] |parent_agency = |child1_agency = |child2_agency = |website = {{url|http://www.tint.or.th}} |footnotes = |map = |map_width = |map_caption = }}
The '''Thailand Institute of Nuclear Technology (TINT)''' ('''Thai name:''' สถาบันเทคโนโลยีนิวเคลียร์แห่งชาติ) is a public organization in [[Bangkok]], [[Thailand]].<ref>http://www.most.go.th/main/en/375-ministry-of-science-and-technology/agencies-under-most/4516-thailand-institute-of-nuclear-technology-public-orga</ref> [[File:TRR1-M1-Reactor.jpg|thumb|TRR1/M1 research reactor at the Thailand Institute of Nuclear Technology]]
==Overview== The institute is an entity established in December 2006 for national nuclear research and development. It is aimed to serve as the research body, cooperating with the [[Office of Atoms for Peace]] (OAP) who serves as the nuclear regulatory body of the country. TINT operates under [[Ministry of Science and Technology (Thailand)|Ministry of Science and Technology]] (MoST) and works closely with OAP and the [[International Atomic Energy Agency]] (IAEA).<ref>http://www.e-science.in.th/infra/index.php/tint</ref>
'''Research programs at TINT:''' # Medical and Public Health # Agricultural # Material and Industrial # Environmental # Advanced Technology
'''Nuclear operations:''' # Safety # Nuclear Engineering # Reactor Operation
